FSRI: Dimensions: 101.50 x 102.34 x 0.86 mm; with frame; with calcium silicate substrate

After ignition an air bubble formed beneath the sample which raised the height of the sample surface. After a few seconds a hole formed in the sample which released the gases in the bubble at high enough velocity to form a horizontal flame that extended beyond the radius of the cone. This only lasted a few seconds, then the sample returned to normal burning behavoir.
